result.execSummary:
The defendant Ulises Landa Leon was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Operate w/o Valid License(3rd+ w/in3Yrs), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.05(3)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Deposit in 15TR1362 shall be applied to fine and costs due in 15CM676 with any balance due within 30 days or civil judgment shall enter.
Defendant shall, within three (3) days, contact the Washington County Sheriff's Department for purposes of supplying a biological specimen for DNA analysis.

Def given complaint, advised of charges, penalties and rights, and probable cause found.   Def waives right to counsel; Court accepts waiver.  Recess.  Reconvene.  Pretrial held; agreement reached.  Def continues atty waiver; Court accepts waiver.  Def acknowledges prior Operate w/out Valid DL convictions.  Def enters guilty plea.  Court finds def guilty.  Statements from State.  Court imposes fine of $579 - $389.50 from 15TR1362 (DRI) to be paid w/in 30 days or judgment shall enter.    Defendant shall, within three (3) days, contact the Washington County Sheriff's Department for purposes of supplying a biological specimen for DNA analysis; Court informs of right to expunction.
